@startuml
title Viaverse Quote / Offer — Use Case Diagram
left to right direction

actor "Worker / Business" as Worker
actor Requester
actor "marketplace-service" as Marketplace
actor "notification-service" as Notification

rectangle "Quote / Offer Boundary" {
  usecase "View matched request" as View
  usecase "Open request detail" as Open
  usecase "Ask clarification\noptional" as Ask
  usecase "Create quote draft" as Draft
  usecase "Set price / estimate" as Price
  usecase "Write offer message" as Message
  usecase "Set start time / duration" as Schedule
  usecase "Send quote" as Send
  usecase "Revise quote" as Revise
  usecase "Withdraw quote" as Withdraw
  usecase "Receive quote" as Receive
  usecase "Compare offers" as Compare
  usecase "Accept quote" as Accept
  usecase "Reject quote" as Reject
  usecase "Emit events\nQuoteSent / QuoteAccepted" as Events
}

Worker --> View
View --> Open
Open --> Ask : optional
Open --> Draft
Draft --> Price
Price --> Message
Message --> Schedule
Schedule --> Send
Send ..> Revise : revision flow
Revise ..> Send : resend
Worker --> Withdraw
Requester --> Receive
Receive --> Compare
Compare --> Accept
Compare --> Reject
Accept --> Events
Marketplace --> Send : persist
Marketplace --> Accept : state change
Notification --> Receive : notify requester

note bottom
Sending quotes/offers is free.
Requester sees quotes for own request only.
Competitor quote details are not visible to other workers/businesses.
end note
@enduml
